extends ../_templates/_normal-layout.pug

block head
    +head('Copyediting')
block header
    h1 Copyediting
block main
    section
        h2 Fiction
        p From September 2022 to June 2023, I served as the prose editor of The Catalyst Contemporary Literary Arts Magazine at UC Santa Barbara. I helped students and outside submitters polish their words, ideas, and stories for publication.
        ul
            li.starred Prose: “The Three Times I Have Dared to Tango With the Tides” (#[a(href='https://platypiduses.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Catalyst-The-Three-Times-I-Have-Dared-to-Tango-With-the-Tides-before.pdf') before] and #[a(href='https://platypiduses.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Catalyst-The-Three-Times-I-Have-Dared-to-Tango-With-the-Tides-after.pdf') after])
            li.starred Prose: “Tarsal Maggot” (#[a(href='https://platypiduses.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Catalyst-Tarsal-Maggot-before.pdf') before] and #[a(href='https://platypiduses.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Catalyst-Tarsal-Maggot-after.pdf') after])
            li.starred Prose: “*Sensitive” (#[a(href='https://platypiduses.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Catalyst-Sensitive-before.pdf') before] and #[a(href='https://platypiduses.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Catalyst-Sensitive-after.pdf') after])
            li Prose: “All Aboard” (#[a(href='https://platypiduses.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Catalyst-All-Aboard-before.pdf') before] and #[a(href='https://platypiduses.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Catalyst-All-Aboard-after.pdf') after])
            li Poetry: “Running Cross Country in Oxnard” (#[a(href='https://platypiduses.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Catalyst-Running-Cross-Country-in-Oxnard-before.pdf') before] and #[a(href='https://platypiduses.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Catalyst-Running-Cross-Country-in-Oxnard-after.pdf') after])
    section
        h2 Press releases and event write-ups
        p From April to June 2023, I interned with #[a(href='https://ivparks.org') Isla Vista Recreation & Park District], writing press releases and event recaps. #[strong I compiled information and interviewed event attendees in a journalistic style]—I was not merely sitting at a desk all day, though I did have practice coming into the office at regularly scheduled hours.
        p #[strong I was also the go-to person whenever someone needed suggestions on their writing], such as with social media posts, newsletters, and the website. To ensure consistency across the organization, I created a style guide of commonly used words and grammatical structures, using as my foundations #[i The Chicago Manual of Style] and #[i Merriam-Webster's Collegiate Dictionary].
        ul
            li.starred #[a(href='https://platypiduses.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/IVRPD-APIDA-Heritage-Month-Celebration-press-release.pdf') Press release: APIDA Heritage Month Celebration]
